(Summary: Non-small cell lung cancer \(NSCLC\) - the most common form of lung cancer - is an) Tj
T*
(aggressive malignancy with limited effective therapeutic options1. Osimertinib, a third-) Tj
T*
(generation epidermal growth factor receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor \(EGFR-TKI\), has) Tj
T*
(revolutionized treatment for EGFR-mutant NSCLC, yet resistance significantly limits its) Tj
T*
(clinical benefit to patients2. Here, using a genome-wide genetic screen, we discover that) Tj
T*
(pyruvate kinase M2 \(PKM2\) is a novel regulator of Osimertinib resistance. Loss of PKM2) Tj
T*
(triggers fatty acid biosynthesis activation in a glycolysis-independent manner. We have shown) Tj
T*
(that PKM2 interacts with KDM1A in cytosol and nuclear translocation of KDM1A is increased in) Tj
T*
(both PKM2-KO and Osimertinib-persister cells. Mechanistically, KDM1A demethylates H3K9me3 in) Tj
T*
(the promoter region of the key lipid synthesis enzyme, fatty acid synthase \(FASN\), and) Tj
T*
(cooperates with transcription factor AP-2 to activate FASN transcription, thereby conferring) Tj
T*
(Osimertinib resistance. Pharmacological inhibition of FASN by Orlistat induces synthetic) Tj
T*
(lethality with Osimertinib in vitro and vivo Osimertinib-resistant models. Treatment of 9) Tj
